    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Cricket score service — getter isMatchLive boolean",
    "instruction": "How do I add an isMatchLive getter to a cricket score service?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\n\nexport default class ScoreService extends Service {\n  @tracked liveScore = null;\n\n  get isMatchLive() { return this.liveScore?.status === 'live'; }\n  get isMatchComplete() { return this.liveScore?.status === 'completed'; }\n  get isMatchUpcoming() { return this.liveScore?.status === 'upcoming'; }\n\n  get matchStatusLabel() {\n    if (this.isMatchLive) return '🔴 Live';\n    if (this.isMatchComplete) return '✅ Completed';\n    if (this.isMatchUpcoming) return '🕐 Upcoming';\n    return 'Unknown';\n  }\n}\n```\nEach status getter reads `@tracked liveScore` so they all recompute reactively. `matchStatusLabel` composes the boolean getters for display, keeping template logic minimal."
  },
  {
    "id": 106,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Player service — @tracked selectedPlayer, selectPlayer() method",
    "instruction": "How do I build a player service with @tracked selectedPlayer and a selectPlayer method?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\n\nexport default class PlayerService extends Service {\n  @tracked selectedPlayer = null;\n\n  selectPlayer(player) { this.selectedPlayer = player; }\n  deselectPlayer() { this.selectedPlayer = null; }\n\n  get hasSelectedPlayer() { return this.selectedPlayer !== null; }\n\n  isSelected(playerId) {\n    return this.selectedPlayer?.id === playerId;\n  }\n}\n```\n`selectPlayer` takes a player object — not just an ID — so components can immediately render name, stats etc without a separate lookup. `isSelected(id)` lets each player card know if it should show highlight state."
  },
  {
    "id": 107,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Player service — fetchPlayer(id) task, caches result in @tracked map",
    "instruction": "How do I write a fetchPlayer task that caches results in a @tracked object map?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\nimport { task } from 'ember-concurrency';\n\nexport default class PlayerService extends Service {\n  @tracked playerCache = {};\n\n  fetchPlayer = task(async (playerId) => {\n    if (this.playerCache[playerId]) return this.playerCache[playerId];\n    const response = await fetch(`/api/players/${playerId}`);\n    const player = await response.json();\n    this.playerCache = { ...this.playerCache, [playerId]: player };\n    return player;\n  });\n\n  getPlayer(playerId) { return this.playerCache[playerId] ?? null; }\n}\n```\nReturn early from cache to avoid redundant API calls. Update `playerCache` using spread to create a new object reference — plain mutation won't trigger reactivity. `getPlayer` is a synchronous accessor for already-loaded data."
  },
  {
    "id": 108,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Player service — clearSelection() method",
    "instruction": "How do I add a clearSelection method to a player service?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\n\nexport default class PlayerService extends Service {\n  @tracked selectedPlayer = null;\n  @tracked playerCache = {};\n\n  clearSelection() {\n    this.selectedPlayer = null;\n  }\n\n  clearCache() {\n    this.playerCache = {};\n  }\n\n  resetAll() {\n    this.clearSelection();\n    this.clearCache();\n  }\n}\n```\nSeparating `clearCache` allows a cache flush without losing the current selection. `resetAll` is for full state teardown — useful when navigating away from a team selection screen."
  },
  {
    "id": 109,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Match service — @tracked currentMatch, loadMatch(id) task",
    "instruction": "How do I create a match service with @tracked currentMatch and a loadMatch task?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\nimport { task } from 'ember-concurrency';\n\nexport default class MatchService extends Service {\n  @tracked currentMatch = null;\n  @tracked isLoading = false;\n  @tracked error = null;\n\n  loadMatch = task(async (matchId) => {\n    this.isLoading = true;\n    this.error = null;\n    this.currentMatch = null;\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch(`/api/matches/${matchId}`);\n      if (!response.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}`);\n      this.currentMatch = await response.json();\n    } catch (err) {\n      this.error = err.message;\n    } finally {\n      this.isLoading = false;\n    }\n  });\n}\n```\nClear `currentMatch` at the start to avoid showing stale data while the new one loads. The `if (!response.ok)` check converts HTTP errors into thrown errors. `finally` guarantees `isLoading` resets."
  },
  {
    "id": 110,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Match service — @tracked recentMatches array",
    "instruction": "How do I add @tracked recentMatches to a match service with a fetch task?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\nimport { task } from 'ember-concurrency';\n\nexport default class MatchService extends Service {\n  @tracked recentMatches = [];\n\n  fetchRecentMatches = task(async (teamId, limit = 5) => {\n    const response = await fetch(`/api/teams/${teamId}/matches?limit=${limit}&sort=desc`);\n    const { matches } = await response.json();\n    this.recentMatches = matches;\n  });\n\n  get lastMatch() { return this.recentMatches.at(0) ?? null; }\n  get winCount() { return this.recentMatches.filter((m) => m.result === 'win').length; }\n}\n```\n`recentMatches` defaults to `[]` so template `#each` loops don't crash before data loads. `.at(0)` retrieves the most recent match. `winCount` derives reactively from the tracked array."
  },
  {
    "id": 111,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Match service — getter hasActiveMatch boolean",
    "instruction": "How do I write a hasActiveMatch getter on a match service?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\n\nexport default class MatchService extends Service {\n  @tracked currentMatch = null;\n\n  get hasActiveMatch() {\n    return this.currentMatch !== null && this.currentMatch.status === 'live';\n  }\n\n  get matchTitle() {\n    if (!this.currentMatch) return 'No Match';\n    const { team1, team2, venue } = this.currentMatch;\n    return `${team1} vs ${team2} at ${venue}`;\n  }\n\n  get isMatchLoaded() { return this.currentMatch !== null; }\n}\n```\n`hasActiveMatch` combines null check with status check — a match must both exist and be live. `matchTitle` uses destructuring and a template literal. All getters are reactive via `@tracked currentMatch`."
  },
  {
    "id": 112,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Tournament service — @tracked activeTournament, @tracked standings",
    "instruction": "How do I create a tournament service with @tracked activeTournament and standings?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\n\nexport default class TournamentService extends Service {\n  @tracked activeTournament = null;\n  @tracked standings = [];\n  @tracked isLoadingStandings = false;\n\n  get tournamentName() { return this.activeTournament?.name ?? 'Select Tournament'; }\n  get totalTeams() { return this.standings.length; }\n\n  setActiveTournament(tournament) {\n    this.activeTournament = tournament;\n    this.standings = [];\n  }\n}\n```\nClearing `standings` when a new tournament is selected prevents stale data. `tournamentName` uses optional chaining with a readable fallback. `totalTeams` derives reactively from standings length."
  },
  {
    "id": 113,
    "layer": "syntax",
    "topic": "Tournament service — fetchStandings() task",
    "instruction": "How do I write a fetchStandings task in a tournament service?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';\nimport { task } from 'ember-concurrency';\n\nexport default class TournamentService extends Service {\n  @tracked standings = [];\n  @tracked activeTournament = null;\n\n  fetchStandings = task(async () => {\n    if (!this.activeTournament) return;\n    const response = await fetch(`/api/tournaments/${this.activeTournament.id}/standings`);\n    const { standings } = await response.json();\n    this.standings = standings.sort((a, b) => b.points - a.points);\n  });\n}\n```\nGuard with `if (!this.activeTournament) return` to avoid fetching without an ID. Sort descending by points immediately so consuming components always get sorted data."
