    "topic": "Config service — read-only getters for environment config values",
    "instruction": "How do I create a config service with read-only getters for environment configuration?",
    "response": "```js\nimport Service from '@ember/service';\nimport config from 'spordium-web/config/environment';\n\nexport default class ConfigService extends Service {\n  get apiBaseUrl() { return config.APP.apiBaseUrl; }\n  get wsUrl() { return config.APP.websocketUrl; }\n  get isProduction() { return config.environment === 'production'; }\n  get isDevelopment() { return config.environment === 'development'; }\n\n  get featureFlags() {\n    return Object.freeze({ ...config.APP.featureFlags });\n  }\n}\n```\nRead-only getters prevent accidental mutation of config values. `Object.freeze` on `featureFlags` makes the returned object immutable. Wrapping ENV imports in a service makes config mockable in tests via `this.owner.register('service:config', MockConfigService)`."
